<Base
  title="Estate & Probate Appraisals in Las Vegas | Las Vegas Appraisal Co."
  description="Estate and probate appraisals in Las Vegas. Date-of-death, current market value, and retrospective valuations. IRS and court compliant. Call (702) 894-9279."
  canonical="https://lvappraisalco.com/estate-probate-appraisals"
>

  <div class="service-page-header">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Estate & Probate Appraisals</p>
      <h1>Estate & Probate Appraisals in Las Vegas</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.05rem;">
        Accurate valuations for families and legal professionals.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="service-content">
      <p>When a loved one passes away, settling their estate often requires an accurate appraisal of their real property. Las Vegas Appraisal Co. specializes in estate and probate appraisals, providing certified valuations that meet Nevada court requirements and IRS standards — delivered with the care and professionalism that sensitive situations demand.</p>

      <h2>Types of Estate Appraisals We Provide</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Date-of-Death Appraisals:</strong> A retrospective valuation as of the date the owner passed away, required for estate tax filings and probate proceedings.</li>
        <li><strong>Current Market Value Appraisals:</strong> Used when heirs plan to sell, refinance, or distribute property after the estate is settled.</li>
        <li><strong>Retrospective Appraisals:</strong> Historical valuations for any past date, useful in trust administration or tax disputes.</li>
        <li><strong>Trust Administration Appraisals:</strong> Required when real property is transferred into or out of a trust.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Accuracy Matters in Estate Appraisals</h2>
      <p>An inaccurate estate appraisal can have serious tax consequences. Overvaluing a property inflates estate taxes; undervaluing it can trigger IRS audits and penalties. Our certified appraisers produce defensible, USPAP-compliant reports that stand up to scrutiny from the IRS, Nevada probate courts, and other legal authorities.</p>

      <h2>Working With Attorneys and Executors</h2>
      <p>We regularly work with estate attorneys, executors, trustees, and financial advisors throughout Clark County. We understand the legal requirements and timelines involved in probate proceedings, and we make the process as smooth as possible for everyone involved.</p>

      <h2>Compassionate, Professional Service</h2>
      <p>We approach every estate appraisal with sensitivity and professionalism. We coordinate directly with family members or legal representatives to schedule inspections at a convenient time, and we deliver clear, complete reports that minimize confusion during an already difficult time.</p>

      <h2>Service Area & Turnaround</h2>
      <p>We serve all of Clark County and typically deliver estate appraisal reports within 2–5 business days. Expedited service is available upon request.</p>

      <div class="service-cta">
        <p>Available 7 days a week.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="tel:+17028949279" class="btn btn-primary">(702) 894-9279</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Request a Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
